The '''Barefoot College''' in [[Tilonia]], [[Rajasthan]], [[India]], is based on [[Mahatma Gandhi]]'s ideas of development.

In 2003 [[Bunker Roy]], the founder of the Barefoot College won the St Andrews Prize for the Environment{{w|St Andrews Prize for the Environment}} for bringing solar energy to remote Himalayan villages, using "barefoot engineers".

